originalText.text:
If you want your car scratched, covered in bird droppings then have the attendant scream at you for suggesting that the car was scratched, then rush over with polish (that wasn't asked for or wanted) and buff your car to try and hide the scratch that had appeared, you have found the place.
My car had just been collected from the Audi dealership after it's annual service. I am very careful to always check the car when collected from anywhere and can 100% say it was in the same or better condition than when I had dropped it off. They also valet the car at the end of the service so it is in great condition. From there I drove straight to the parking lot. This was my first night in a new monthly lease, done through a parking app.
When I went to collect the car the next day, the car was not out front, as you would expect and like the other people's cars were. This was the first strange thing, the attendant then jumped out of the car, after delivering and went straight to the booth. My wife jumped in the driver side and I done a quick lap of the car to inspect. Immediately I saw a light scuff on the pax front door and a straight, longer scratch on the upper hood pax side. I did the usual light dry finger rub then wet my finger to remove. Neither removed the marks. I then asked the attendant why my car was scratched. At this point he explodes into a fit of rage, (as previously mentioned in comments). The conversation then had absolutely no substance because this guy was just irrational. As I was taking photos of the scratch, the attendant then approached with what I can only guess was polish, but can't confirm either way what it was. (you can see him coming In the photo). This was a clear way to try to remove the scratches that had appeared on my car.
While I will agree the scratches were not very deep, they are and were still completely not acceptable. We put our car in a garage, at a risk during the pandemic, due to worrying about scratches on the street and these guys done exactly the opposite of what we wanted!
The final nail in the coffin is after we leave the garage, I call the company to complain, the most uninterested operator answers and can't wait to transfer over the call to claims department, who don't answer. I stayed ringing on my own and wife's phone for 20 mins straight and no answer.
These guys are extremely shady operators, stay away at your own risk.
It looks like someone slid along our car and scuffed a shoe on the pax door, if this is the way they are treating people's cars, I will take my chances parking elsewhere.

originalText.text: DON'T park here!  Purchased parking via ParkWhiz for 8 hours but only intended to park for 2 hrs.  As I pulled into the garage, the attendant ran out and told me that if I am using a 3rd party parking voucher, I cannot because his "system is down".  It was clear that his "system" was NOT down.  He wasted my time to have look for other parking alternatives in UES!  If you have no intention of honoring ParkWhiz vouchers then DON'T participate.  I will not consider this garage in the future!
